adflib (0.10.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Some changes in the API (refactoring, renaming etc.).
  * Improved device support (hard disks, size limits, predefined types).
  * Renamed and improved command-line utilities.
  * Bugfixes: write support (OFS data block update on appending), Linux
    native device driver (opening device), unadf (setting file
    permissions and timestamps on directories).
  * More details on changes in ChangeLog and git log.

 -- Tomasz Wolak <tomas.wolak@gmail.com>  Sun, 27 Apr 2025 18:18:20 +0100


adflib (0.9.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Library license changed to dual license (GPL2 and LGPL2.1).
  * Many changes in the API (refactoring, renaming etc.).
  * Improved support of block allocation bitmap (checking and reconstruction).
  * Improved device API (added ramdisk and a possibility to implement others).
  * Improved salvage, added an utility for undeleting files (EXPERIMENTAL!).
  * Bugfixes: bitmap, memory leaks and others (more in ChangeLog and git log).

 -- Tomasz Wolak <tomas.wolak@gmail.com>  Thu, 16 May 2024 17:19:35 +0100


